"""Substrate string-table ГўВЂВ” cross-process-stable string interning. The hash-based allocation used previously for string-recipe instances (`abs(hash(value)) % (10**9) + 1`) works in-process but is NOT cross- process stable. Python's hash() is salted differently per process by default ГўВЂВ” a pattern serialized in process A would not match the same pattern serialized in process B. This module is the substrate-resident replacement. Each unique string gets a sequentially-allocated instance number that persists in the database. The same string in any process gets the same instance. Used by: - form_rules.py ГѓВѓГ‚ВўГѓВ‚Г‚ВЂГѓВ‚Г‚В” for IdentCapture name encoding, RepeatedCapture name encoding, Sequence/Repeat markers - form_builders.py ГѓВѓГ‚ВўГѓВ‚Г‚ВЂГѓВ‚Г‚В” for Build/CaptureRef name encoding, template markers - markdown_frontend.py ГѓВѓГ‚ВўГѓВ‚Г‚ВЂГѓВ‚Г‚В” for frontmatter shape encoding (future) The legacy `_STRING_CACHE` dict in form_rules.py becomes a per-process shortcut: populated by interning, consulted by reverse-lookup. The substrate is the source of truth. """ __future__ annotations  typing Optional  sqlalchemy Column  Integer  Text  UniqueConstraint  sqlalchemy.orm Session  app.services.unified_db Base  class SubstrateStringORM(Base): """One row per unique string ever seen. The `instance` column is the auto-allocated sequence number. `value` is unique and indexed for round-trip lookup. """ __tablename__ "substrate_strings" instance Column(Integer, primary_key=True, autoincrement=True) value Column(Text, nullable=False) __table_args__ ( UniqueConstraint("value", name "uq_substrate_strings_value"), ) intern_string_instance session: Session, value: str """Get the substrate-resident instance for `value`. Allocates if new. Cross-process stable: the same string always returns the same instance, regardless of which process or session interned it first. Within a single process, the instance is assigned by the database's auto-increment counter (or by allocate-on-first-insert when no AUTOINCREMENT is available). """ existing ( session.query(SubstrateStringORM) .filter_by(value value) .one_or_none() ) if existing is not None: return existing.instance row SubstrateStringORM(value=value) session.add(row) try: session.flush() return row.instance except Exception: session.rollback() existing ( session.query(SubstrateStringORM) .filter_by(value value) .one_or_none() ) if existing is None: raise return existing.instance lookup_string_value session: Session, instance: int """Reverse lookup: given an instance number, return the original string.""" row ( session.query(SubstrateStringORM) .filter_by(instance instance) .one_or_none() ) return row.value if row is not None else None list_strings session: Session """Enumerate the string-table for inspection.""" rows session.query(SubstrateStringORM).all() return [(r.instance, r.value) for r in rows]
